The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Sri Lanka pick Dilhara 
	 - CHAMPIONS TROPHY Colombo: Sri Lanka named paceman Dilhara Fernando to their 14-man squad on Tuesday for next months ICC Champions Trophy in England. Fernando, 25, replaces middle-order batsman Thilina Kandamby in the only change to Sri Lankas victorious Asia Cup squad. New Zealand chose seam bowler Kyle Mills ahead of James Franklin in their Champions Trophy squad, says a report from Auckland. Coach John Bracewell said that Mills will offer more flexibility than Franklin, who did well after being called into the squad following a spate of injuries on the recent tour of England. LANKA SQUAD Maravan Atapattu (captain), Sanath Jayasuriya, Kumar Sangakkara, Mahela Jayawardene, Tillekeratne Dilshan, Chaminda Vaas, Farveez Maharoof, Lasith Malinga, Muttiah Muralidharan, Nuwan Zoysa, Dilhara Fernando, Saman Jayantha, Avishka Gunawardene, Upul Chandana. NZ SQUAD Stephen Fleming (captain), Nathan Astle, Ian Butler, Chris Cairns, Chris Harris, Hamish Marshall, Brendan McCullum, Craig McMillan, Kyle Mills, Jacob Oram, Michael Papps, Scott Styris, Daryl Tuffey, Daniel Vettori. (Reuters)  Copyright 
